Use git merge when:

You want to preserve a clear history with separate merge commits.
Collaborating with a team where a linear history is not a strict requirement.
Use git rebase when:

You want a linear history without additional merge commits.
Working on a feature branch and want to incorporate changes from the main branch into your feature branch.
